{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A black car pulls up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two ARMY OFFICERS get out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EDWARD (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: And so it was no surprise that the Army believed I was dead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hearing the news, Sandra CRIES OUT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The pain of her shout makes church bells RING.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BEHIND THE TEMPLETON HOUSE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sandra hangs sheets to dry on the clotheslines, forming a tunnel of fabric.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EDWARD (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: After four months, Sandra had gotten over the worst of the nightmares.
{DIALOGUE}: When the phone rang, she didn't think it was somehow me calling her.
{DIALOGUE}: When a car drove past, she didn't get up to check out the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pulling a dress out of the basket, Sandra looks up to see
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A MAN'S SILHOUETTE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: on the sheet in front of her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She freezes, watching the shadow ripple across the white fabric, blowing so softly in the breeze.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She knows it can't be him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's dead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With all the strength she can gather, she hangs up that dress and digs another one out of the basket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looking up, she sees not a shadow but Edward himself standing before her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She GASPS, disbelieving, but his hand is real.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is destiny.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Without another moment's hesitation, she kisses him.
{META_DATA}: CROSSFADE TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BRIGHT SUNLIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: filters through soft sheets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We're under the covers, where a man's hand traces the curves of a woman's bare back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A beat, then she turns over in bed, revealing her to be
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JOSEPHINE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She blinks slowly, just waking up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Will is watching her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's been up for a while.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We are actually...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. WILL AND JOSEPHINE'S ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...where the couple stays cocooned under the sheets, a kind of limbo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A kiss good morning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Legs entangling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Neither wants to get up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOSEPHINE
{DIALOGUE}: I talked with your father last night.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WILL
{DIALOGUE}: Did you?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A look to say, should I be worried?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOSEPHINE
{DIALOGUE}: You never told me how your parents met.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WILL
{DIALOGUE}: They met at Auburn.
